content: This is a really good app to keep your scores and stats pins. The onky reason I really didn't give it 4 stars is because It would be nice if it totaled all the games for that session.
This is a great app however i would loke to see a max score feature added. Everyone does not know how to calculate their score. This feature can aid in learning how to do the math. Thanks
Great way to help my game and keep score.
Sometimes the game does not capture all of my games at the end of a set.

Like the app, I would like it even more if also kept stats of amount of covered frames, ie sum of spare and strike percentage. It would also bore intuitive if the spare percentage calculation did not include frames that were strikes, and or holes. Currently a low spare percentage could just mean that I striked alot :/ These changes would change my rating to a solid 5 star!

Is it possible to add a send data button under settings? For Android to backup, save data, email to yourself, open my files, search backup, copy to bowling scorer folder, open app, settings, restore. Awesome app! Thanks
Would be great if it showed series and best/strike out score.

I wish it saved it to the SD card like it says it does (but doeant) and 
also total each Event.

IMO best of the available. Missing some features others have, but the graphs and analyses available here are some of the best and offer serious bowlers the most relevant information. Two things: 1. Game for some reason calls itself Bowling Scrorer; 2. The Event selection in the Graphs shows only the month and year instead of the full date.
Was good before the purchased version. Now after I bought it every time I open it, it asks me to purchase the full version. So I have to go to the play store and open it there
Is there anyway to add series scores per event? Also add 600+ series,  700+ series,  etc.?

The app works good for keeping scores and stats.  However I bought the paid version so I could restore my data to a new phone.  Well it lost my data. So basically I wasted my money paying for the app.       Any answer would be great as to why i cant get the data to back up to a sd card
